---

### Recursive Version

```rust
fn fibonacci_recursive(n: u32) -> u32 {
    if n == 0 {
        0
    } else if n == 1 {
        1
    } else {
        fibonacci_recursive(n - 1) + fibonacci_recursive(n - 2)
    }
}

fn main() {
    let n = 10;
    println!("Recursive Fibonacci at position {n}: {}", fibonacci_recursive(n));
}
```

---

### Iterative Version (more efficient)

```rust
fn fibonacci_iterative(n: u32) -> u32 {
    if n == 0 {
        return 0;
    }
    let mut a = 0;
    let mut b = 1;
    for _ in 2..=n {
        let temp = a + b;
        a = b;
        b = temp;
    }
    b
}

fn main() {
    let n = 10;
    println!("Iterative Fibonacci at position {n}: {}", fibonacci_iterative(n));
}
```

---

**How to run:**  
Paste the code in a file named `main.rs` and run with `cargo run` or `rustc main.rs && ./main`.

You can choose either version depending on your requirements. The iterative one is more performant for larger values of `n`.

